TL;DR (Non-Binding Summary)

You may freely use, modify, and experiment with the Nitro Core DX platform for non-commercial purposes

You own 100% of the games and software you create for Nitro Core DX

You may sell your games without permission

The emulator, architecture, and hardware implementations are not commercial-use free

Any commercial use of the platform itself (software or hardware) requires permission

This summary is informational only. The full license below governs.

1. Scope and Definitions

This license governs the Nitro Core DX Platform, which includes:

Emulator source code

System architecture and design

Instruction set architecture (ISA)

Memory maps and hardware behavior

Official tools, documentation, and reference implementations

This license does not apply to original software, games, or applications created to run on Nitro Core DX.

2. Non-Commercial Platform License

Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person obtaining a copy of the Nitro Core DX Platform (the “Platform”) to use, copy, modify, and experiment with the Platform for non-commercial purposes only, subject to the following conditions.

You MAY:

Study, modify, and experiment with the Platform

Fork and redistribute the Platform for non-commercial use

Create compilers, tools, debuggers, or development utilities

Use the Platform for education, research, or hobby projects

Run the Platform on personal devices, emulators, or test hardware

You MUST:

Retain this license and copyright notice

Credit Nitro Core DX as the original platform

Clearly indicate if the Platform has been modified

You MAY NOT:

Sell, license, or monetize the Platform

Bundle the Platform with paid products or services

Use the Platform in commercial distributions without permission

3. Ownership of Games and Software

Any original game, application, or software written to run on Nitro Core DX is:

Fully owned by its creator

Not subject to this license

Free to be licensed, sold, or distributed under any terms chosen by its author

This includes:

Commercial games

Freeware and open-source software

Demos, tools, and utilities

No permission is required to sell or distribute such software.

4. Encouraged Attribution (Optional)

Developers are encouraged, but not required, to acknowledge Nitro Core DX as the target platform for their software (for example: “Built for Nitro Core DX”).

This is voluntary and non-binding.

5. Platform Ownership and Reserved Rights

The Nitro Core DX Platform remains the exclusive intellectual property of the copyright holder.

This includes:

Emulator implementations

System architecture and specifications

Instruction set and memory design

Official development tools and documentation

All rights not expressly granted are reserved.

6. Hardware and FPGA Restrictions

The following apply regardless of modification level:

FPGA, ASIC, or hardware implementations of Nitro Core DX may be created only for personal, educational, or research purposes

Commercial manufacture, sale, licensing, or distribution of hardware implementations requires explicit written permission

This includes:

FPGA bitstreams

HDL implementations

Physical consoles or embedded systems

Development kits or boards

All commercial hardware rights are expressly reserved.

