Developer FAQ (Informational)

Can I sell my game?
Yes. Games and software you write for Nitro Core DX are yours to sell.

Do I need permission to publish a game?
No.

Can I open-source my game?
Yes. You choose your own license.

Can I fork the emulator and sell it?
No, not without a Commercial Platform License.

Can I build FPGA hardware for myself?
Yes, for personal or educational use only.

Can I sell FPGA or hardware implementations?
No, not without permission.

Does this license claim ownership of my code?
No. Your software remains yours.

License Philosophy (Non-Binding)

Nitro Core DX is intended to be a developer-friendly platform that encourages experimentation, creativity, and commercial software creation while preserving the integrity and long-term stewardship of the underlying system.

This license separates platform ownership from software ownership to ensure developers benefit directly from their work while allowing the platform to evolve responsibly, including future hardware implementations.